### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@studentId = 1

### ====================================
### 1. CREATE (POST) - Add a new student
### ====================================

### Create Student 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "age": 20,
  "major": "Computer Science"
}

### Create Student 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Smith",
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "age": 21,
  "major": "Engineering"
}

### Create Student 3
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob Wilson",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "age": 19,
  "major": "Mathematics"
}

### ====================================
### 2. READ (GET) - Retrieve students
### ====================================

### Get all students
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/students

### Get student by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/students/{{studentId}}

### Get student by ID (change this to test different IDs)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/students/2

### ====================================
### 3. UPDATE (PUT) - Update entire student
### ====================================

### Update Student (Full Update)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/students/{{studentId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Updated",
  "email": "john.updated@example.com",
  "age": 21,
  "major": "Data Science"
}

### ====================================
### 4. UPDATE (PATCH) - Partial update
### ====================================

### Partial Update - Change only age
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/students/{{studentId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "age": 22
}

### Partial Update - Change only major
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/students/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "major": "Physics"
}

### ====================================
### 5. DELETE - Remove a student
### ====================================

### Delete a student
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/students/{{studentId}}

### Delete another student
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/students/3

### ====================================
### PRACTICE EXERCISES
### ====================================

### Exercise 1: Try creating a student without required fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Student"
}

### Exercise 2: Try retrieving a non-existent student
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/students/999

### Exercise 3: Try deleting a non-existent student
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/students/999

### Exercise 4: Try creating a duplicate email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Duplicate Email",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "age": 25,
  "major": "Biology"
}
